"use strict";(globalThis.webpackChunkbytesofpurpose_blog=globalThis.webpackChunkbytesofpurpose_blog||[]).push([[34328],{14371:e=>{e.exports=JSON.parse('{"archive":{"blogPosts":[{"id":"about-my-thoughts","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/about-my-thoughts","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2026-06-25-about-my-thoughts.mdx","source":"@site/thoughts/2026-06-25-about-my-thoughts.mdx","title":"\ud83d\udcad About My Thoughts","description":"Ideas that occurred to me but I have not acted on yet, and the kinds they come in: ideas, simulations, predictions, critiques, and designs.","date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"thoughts","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/thoughts"},{"inline":true,"label":"meta","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/meta"},{"inline":true,"label":"legend","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/legend"}],"readingTime":1.31,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"about-my-thoughts","title":"\ud83d\udcad About My Thoughts","sidebar_label":"\ud83d\udcad About","description":"Ideas that occurred to me but I have not acted on yet, and the kinds they come in: ideas, simulations, predictions, critiques, and designs.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["thoughts","meta","legend"],"date":"2026-06-25T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"legend","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build a NotePlan Plugin?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-noteplan-plugin"}},"content":"This is where I keep the **ideas that occurred to me** but I have not acted on yet. The raw mental\\nevents: a thing I might build, a hypothetical I am playing out, a bet I am making, a critique that\\ncame to mind. Not the dated things I actually did (those are [Initiatives](/initiatives)), not the\\ninputs I keep to shape how I think (those are [Mindset](/mindset)), and not the distilled lessons\\nthat held up over time (those are [Craft](/craft)). Just the thoughts, as they occurred.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## A thought has three ways to graduate\\n\\nA thought is a candidate, not a commitment. Where it ends up depends on what I do with it:\\n\\n- If I **act on it**, it becomes a dated [Initiative](/initiatives).\\n- If I **deliberately keep it to shape how I think**, it becomes part of my [Mindset](/mindset).\\n- If it **distills into a lesson that keeps holding up**, it graduates into [Craft](/craft).\\n\\nThe difference is **occurrence vs. curation**. A quote that just *occurred* to me is a Thought;\\n*keeping* it because it moves me is [Mindset](/mindset). A question that crossed my mind is a\\nThought; the deliberate *set* I ask, on purpose, becomes one of my [Questions](/questions). The\\nthought is the raw event; the curated thing it becomes is Mindset or Questions.\\n\\n## The kinds of thought\\n\\nEach thought is tagged with its KIND, so you can see at a glance what kind of mental work it is:\\n\\n<ThoughtKindLegend />\\n\\nBrowse the posts below, or jump to the [Ideas board](/craft/product-management/ideas)."},{"id":"my-first-noteplan-plugin","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-noteplan-plugin","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2025-03-02-my-first-noteplan-plugin.mdx","source":"@site/thoughts/2025-03-02-my-first-noteplan-plugin.mdx","title":"Should I Build a NotePlan Plugin?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first NotePlan plugin to help with templates, frontmatter, and emoji picking?","date":"2025-03-02T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"noteplan","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/noteplan"},{"inline":true,"label":"plugin","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/plugin"},{"inline":true,"label":"note-taking","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/note-taking"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"templates","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/templates"},{"inline":true,"label":"first-time","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/first-time"},{"inline":true,"label":"idea","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/idea"}],"readingTime":2.13,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"my-first-noteplan-plugin","title":"Should I Build a NotePlan Plugin?","sidebar_label":"NotePlan plugin?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first NotePlan plugin to help with templates, frontmatter, and emoji picking?","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["noteplan","plugin","note-taking","automation","templates","first-time","idea"],"date":"2025-03-02T10:00","kind":"idea","class":"first-time","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"\ud83d\udcad About My Thoughts","permalink":"/thoughts/about-my-thoughts"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build My First iOS App?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-ios-app"}},"content":"A thought I keep coming back to: **should I build my first NotePlan plugin?** It would help with\\nthe templates, frontmatter, and emoji-picking I do by hand today. I have not committed to it; these\\nare the questions and references I am weighing.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## What would the plugin do?\\n\\n* [ ] Noteplan add shortcuts for /thisweek in my plugin ... >2025-W12\\n\\n* [ ] There is tooling to help build proper plugin ... \\n\\t* [ ] Should I migrate my script over?\\n\\n* [ ] Make a noteplan plugin to help with the emoji picking / templates / front mater creation / etc ...\\n\\t* Can I get the dir of a note ...\\n\\t* Can I set front matter attributes?\\n\\t* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/main/dwertheimer.DateAutomations/plugin.json)\\n\\n* Example of creating a new note ... and getting user input ...  and doing front matter \\n\\t* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/main/jgclark.NoteHelpers/src/newNote.js#L21)\\n\\t* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/tree/main/helpers)\\n\\t\\t* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/main/helpers/userInput.js)\\n\\t\\t* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/main/helpers/NPFrontMatter.js)\\n\\n* Arguments are only useful if plugin called from other plugin ...\\n\\n* [ ] Make various shortcuts to update front matter ..\\n\\t* [ ] Make /cancel-plan\\n\\t* [ ] Make /done-plan\\n\\n* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/main/Flow_Guide.md)\\n* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/tree/b728b13f6cebf24651b8e6dcc190893a8352a439?tab=readme-ov-file)\\n* [GitHub: NotePlan/plugins](https://github.com/NotePlan/plugins/blob/b728b13f6cebf24651b8e6dcc190893a8352a439/helpers/NPFrontMatter.js#L834)\\n\\n\\n# --------\\n\\n* [ ] Noteplan is pretty powerful ... can make notes from a command, send to chat gpt to reorganizr a note, etc ...\\n* [ ] Create command to create a new Personal Plan\\n* [ ] New work plan ...\\n* [ ] New personal habit, etc\\n* [ ] Add a reference \\n\\n* [ ] Use noteplan to record a log of the quran ive done trough the plugin ...\\n* [ ] It should auto add to google drivr tracker? I should have data at the page level .... maybe even a shortcut or button I press??\\n* [ ] Good genai use case to determine hofz? certain things I want to log in a special way to see if I do it frequently\\n\\n\\n\\nnewBlogPost noteplan helper ...\\n Release: npm run release \\"omars-lab.PlanningBuddy\\"\\nnoteplan://x-callback-url/runPlugin?pluginID=omars-lab.PlanningBuddy&command=sayHello\\n\\n\\n# Look into noteplan templates instead for some of this?\\n\\ndocumentation: [help.noteplan.co: 237 Frontmatter](https://help.noteplan.co/article/237-frontmatter)\\ndocumentation: [help.noteplan.co: 148 Run Javascript Code In Your Templates](https://help.noteplan.co/article/148-run-javascript-code-in-your-templates)\\n[noteplan.co: Docs](https://noteplan.co/templates/docs)\\n[noteplan.co: Templating Examples Prompt](https://noteplan.co/templates/docs/templating-examples-prompt)\\n\\n\\n* I should use templates for the content ... and the move command to move it to the right folder based on the frontmatter ..."},{"id":"my-first-ios-app","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-ios-app","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2025-01-01-my-first-ios-app.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2025-01-01-my-first-ios-app.md","title":"Should I Build My First iOS App?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first iOS app, a calendar/dashboard I have wanted to make?","date":"2025-01-01T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ios","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ios"},{"inline":true,"label":"swift","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/swift"},{"inline":true,"label":"mobile","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/mobile"},{"inline":true,"label":"app-development","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/app-development"},{"inline":true,"label":"calendar","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/calendar"},{"inline":true,"label":"first-time","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/first-time"},{"inline":true,"label":"idea","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/idea"}],"readingTime":0.82,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"my-first-ios-app","title":"Should I Build My First iOS App?","sidebar_label":"iOS app?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first iOS app, a calendar/dashboard I have wanted to make?","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ios","swift","mobile","app-development","calendar","first-time","idea"],"date":"2025-01-01T10:00","kind":"idea","class":"first-time","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build a NotePlan Plugin?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-noteplan-plugin"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Mac Menu-Bar App?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-mac-menubar-app"}},"content":"A thought I keep coming back to: **should I build my first iOS app?** A calendar/dashboard I have\\nwanted to make. I have not committed to it; these are the questions and references I am weighing.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Priorities\\n  - I need to make my own ios app\\n\\n  \\n- [ ] Build my first iPhone app ...\\n    - [ ] [appcoda.com: Build Your First App](https://www.appcoda.com/learnswift/build-your-first-app.html)\\n* [ ] Basic IOS App\\n    * [ ] [appcoda.com: Build Your First App](https://www.appcoda.com/learnswift/build-your-first-app.html)\\n\\n\\nIphone Calendar Application \\n- [ ] Should I make my own iPhone calendar app / dashboard ...\\n- [ ] Should I make a web app for this?\\n\\t- [ ] [GitHub: patchthecode/JTAppleCalendar](https://github.com/patchthecode/JTAppleCalendar/wiki/Tutorials)\\n- [ ] Can I make a simple iPhone app that reads files from dropbox \u2026\\n\\t- [ ] How do I build a reusable widget \u2026\\n- [ ] Tap into iCloud rest APIs and make a web app based calendar!\\n\\t- [apple.stackexchange.com: Can I Access Icloud Drive Files From Non Apple Device](https://apple.stackexchange.com/questions/347891/can-i-access-icloud-drive-files-from-non-apple-device)"},{"id":"my-first-mac-menubar-app","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-mac-menubar-app","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2025-01-01-my-first-mac-menubar-app.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2025-01-01-my-first-mac-menubar-app.md","title":"Should I Build a Mac Menu-Bar App?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first macOS menu-bar app to show my NotePlan task counts at a glance?","date":"2025-01-01T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"macos","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/macos"},{"inline":true,"label":"menu-bar","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/menu-bar"},{"inline":true,"label":"app","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/app"},{"inline":true,"label":"noteplan","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/noteplan"},{"inline":true,"label":"swift","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/swift"},{"inline":true,"label":"first-time","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/first-time"},{"inline":true,"label":"idea","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/idea"}],"readingTime":0.65,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"my-first-mac-menubar-app","title":"Should I Build a Mac Menu-Bar App?","sidebar_label":"Menu-bar app?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I build my first macOS menu-bar app to show my NotePlan task counts at a glance?","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["macos","menu-bar","app","noteplan","swift","first-time","idea"],"date":"2025-01-01T10:00","kind":"idea","class":"first-time","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build My First iOS App?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-ios-app"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build Smarter Date-Tag Helpers?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-smarter-date-helpers"}},"content":"A thought I keep coming back to: **should I build my first macOS menu-bar app?** One that shows my\\nNotePlan task counts at a glance. I have not committed to it; these are the questions I am weighing.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Menu Bar App\\n* [ ] What does it take to make a Mac menu bar app with counts of NotePlan\'s tasks today ... and a shortcut to open note plan?\\n\\t* [ ] [sarunw.com: How To Create Macos App Without Storyboard](https://sarunw.com/posts/how-to-create-macos-app-without-storyboard/)\\n\\t* [ ] [sarunw.com: How To Make Macos Menu Bar App](https://sarunw.com/posts/how-to-make-macos-menu-bar-app/)\\n\\t* [ ] [fleetingpixels.com: How To Create A Mac Menu Bar App With Nspopover](https://fleetingpixels.com/blog/2020/6/15/how-to-create-a-mac-menu-bar-app-with-nspopover)"},{"id":"idea-smarter-date-helpers","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-smarter-date-helpers","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-07-08-idea-smarter-date-helpers.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-07-08-idea-smarter-date-helpers.md","title":"Should I Build Smarter Date-Tag Helpers?","description":"Upgrade the date-tag tooling: a non-recursive \\"today\\" substituter, \\"next workday\\" and \\"next weekend\\" tags, and a cron that auto-stamps ideas with capture dates.","date":"2022-07-08T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"dates","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/dates"},{"inline":true,"label":"tooling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/tooling"}],"readingTime":0.97,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-smarter-date-helpers","title":"Should I Build Smarter Date-Tag Helpers?","sidebar_label":"Date helpers?","description":"Upgrade the date-tag tooling: a non-recursive \\"today\\" substituter, \\"next workday\\" and \\"next weekend\\" tags, and a cron that auto-stamps ideas with capture dates.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","dates","tooling"],"date":"2022-07-08T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Mac Menu-Bar App?","permalink":"/thoughts/my-first-mac-menubar-app"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Track Which of My Scripts I Actually Use?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-track-script-usage"}},"content":"My auto-expanding date tags (`>2022-01-12` and friends) work, but the substituter is naive. A\\nfew targeted upgrades would make the system trustworthy enough to lean on.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** Make the date-tag helpers smarter:\\n\\n- a non-recursive \\"today\\" substituter (the current one re-expands things it already touched);\\n- a \\"next workday\\" mode (skip weekends when expanding);\\n- a \\"next weekend\\" date tag;\\n- a cron job on the date expander that auto-tags new ideas with their capture date, so every\\n  captured thought carries the date I first had it without me typing it.\\n\\nThat last one is what would make a backlog like this self-dating: the earliest date on an idea\\nbecomes real data instead of something I reconstruct later.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Rewrite the \\"today\\" substituter to be idempotent (non-recursive): expanding an already\\n      expanded line is a no-op.\\n- [ ] Add a \\"next workday\\" expansion mode (Mon-Fri aware).\\n- [ ] Add a \\"next weekend\\" date tag.\\n- [ ] Add a cron job that stamps newly captured ideas with their capture date automatically.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- Re-running the expander never double-expands a line.\\n- New captures get a capture-date tag with no manual step."},{"id":"idea-track-script-usage","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-track-script-usage","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-05-07-idea-track-script-usage.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-05-07-idea-track-script-usage.md","title":"Should I Track Which of My Scripts I Actually Use?","description":"A board-ready idea: instrument my shell functions to log how often each is used, so I can confidently retire the dead ones, and turn the instrumentation into a reusable technique.","date":"2022-05-07T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"self-quantifying","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/self-quantifying"}],"readingTime":2.07,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-track-script-usage","title":"Should I Track Which of My Scripts I Actually Use?","kind":"idea","sidebar_label":"Script usage?","description":"A board-ready idea: instrument my shell functions to log how often each is used, so I can confidently retire the dead ones, and turn the instrumentation into a reusable technique.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","self-quantifying"],"date":"2022-05-07T00:00:00.000Z","draft":false,"board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low"},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build Smarter Date-Tag Helpers?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-smarter-date-helpers"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Auto-Surface My Other Work Streams?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-other-work-streams"}},"content":"A captured idea, matured into something I could actually act on. It started as one line in a\\nbacklog (\\"track script usage: list every function, record how often each is used, retire the\\nunused ones\\"). Here is the firmed-up version.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**Motivation.** Three things at once: years of shell functions have piled up and I cannot tell\\nwhich are dead weight; when I refactor or document my tooling I have no signal for which scripts\\nearn their place; and I am genuinely curious which tools I actually reach for (it fits the\\nbroader \\"quantify yourself\\" thread).\\n\\n**Value.** Two concrete payoffs. First, usage data lets me delete unused functions without fear,\\nshrinking the toolset and making it maintainable. Second, the instrumentation itself (wrapping\\nshell functions to log usage) is a reusable, blog-worthy technique. If I do not do it, nothing\\nbreaks, but the cruft keeps growing and the toolset stays murky. The cost is modest: a logging\\nwrapper plus a tally script.\\n\\n**Scope.** v1 is just my own interactive shell functions on one machine, logging a timestamp and\\nfunction name to a local file, with a script that tallies counts. Explicitly OUT of v1: syncing\\nacross machines, tracking external binaries (only my functions), and any dashboard or\\nvisualization.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Spike: list every shell function I define (`declare -F` / parse the dotfiles).\\n- [ ] Decide the logging mechanism: wrap functions so each invocation appends `timestamp,name`\\n      to a usage log (a `DEBUG` trap or generated wrappers). Pick one in the spike.\\n- [ ] Implement the wrapper/instrumentation for the function set.\\n- [ ] Write a tally script: usage counts per function over a window, sorted, with never-used\\n      functions called out.\\n- [ ] Run it for a few weeks of real usage, then review the never-used list and retire the\\n      dead ones.\\n- [ ] If the wrapper pattern is clean, write it up as a durable scripting technique in `/craft`.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- I can produce a sorted \\"how often each function was used in the last N weeks\\" report on demand.\\n- After a review window, I retire at least the clearly-never-used functions with confidence.\\n- Done enough when the report exists and I have done one retirement pass; abandon if the logging\\n  overhead is annoying in daily use or the data does not change any decision.\\n\\n## Open questions\\n\\n- Trap-based logging vs generated wrappers: which is less intrusive in an interactive shell?\\n  (Needs the spike.)\\n- Is per-invocation logging cheap enough to leave on permanently, or only during a measurement\\n  window?"},{"id":"idea-other-work-streams","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-other-work-streams","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-27-idea-other-work-streams.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-27-idea-other-work-streams.md","title":"Should I Auto-Surface My Other Work Streams?","description":"Auto-generate an \\"other work streams\\" file from every note carrying a \\"today\\" tag, so my active threads stay visible in one place instead of scattered.","date":"2022-04-27T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"notes","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/notes"},{"inline":true,"label":"productivity","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/productivity"}],"readingTime":0.79,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-other-work-streams","title":"Should I Auto-Surface My Other Work Streams?","sidebar_label":"Work streams?","description":"Auto-generate an \\"other work streams\\" file from every note carrying a \\"today\\" tag, so my active threads stay visible in one place instead of scattered.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","notes","productivity"],"date":"2022-04-27T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Track Which of My Scripts I Actually Use?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-track-script-usage"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Make My Browser Bookmarks Portable?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-bookmark-portability"}},"content":"My active work is scattered across whatever notes I happened to be in. I want a single view of\\n\\"what I am currently working on\\" that builds itself from the notes I have already tagged.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** An \\"other work streams\\" file, auto-generated from notes carrying a \\"today\\" tag.\\nAnything I have flagged as today\'s work, anywhere in the book, gets pulled into one file so the\\nthreads I am actively running are visible together instead of buried in their home notes.\\n\\nThis rides on the same \\"today\\"-tag mover the date-tag system already uses; it is a second\\nconsumer of that signal.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Scan the notes for the \\"today\\" tag.\\n- [ ] Aggregate the tagged items into a generated \\"other work streams\\" file.\\n- [ ] Regenerate it on the same trigger the today-mover runs on (on note open, not blind cron).\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- One file always reflects every currently-tagged work stream, with no manual upkeep."},{"id":"idea-bookmark-portability","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-bookmark-portability","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-18-idea-bookmark-portability.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-18-idea-bookmark-portability.md","title":"Should I Make My Browser Bookmarks Portable?","description":"Export browser bookmarks from one browser via the command line and import them into another, so switching browsers does not mean leaving my bookmarks behind.","date":"2022-04-18T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"browser","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/browser"},{"inline":true,"label":"tooling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/tooling"}],"readingTime":0.51,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-bookmark-portability","title":"Should I Make My Browser Bookmarks Portable?","sidebar_label":"Bookmark export?","description":"Export browser bookmarks from one browser via the command line and import them into another, so switching browsers does not mean leaving my bookmarks behind.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","browser","tooling"],"date":"2022-04-18T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Auto-Surface My Other Work Streams?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-other-work-streams"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build an Alias Finder for My Commands?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-alias-finder"}},"content":"Switching browsers always strands my bookmarks. The export/import is doable through the UI, but\\nit is manual and lossy. I want it scriptable.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** A command-line path to export browser bookmarks from one browser and import them\\ninto another, so moving between browsers (or keeping two in sync) is a script, not an afternoon\\nof clicking.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Read/export bookmarks from the source browser\'s store via the command line.\\n- [ ] Transform to the destination browser\'s import format.\\n- [ ] Import into the destination browser.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- A single command moves my bookmarks from one browser to another with nothing lost."},{"id":"idea-alias-finder","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-alias-finder","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-alias-finder.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-alias-finder.md","title":"Should I Build an Alias Finder for My Commands?","description":"A tool that scans all my commands and proposes sensible two-letter acronym aliases, so the helpers I reach for most get short names without me inventing them.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"shell","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/shell"},{"inline":true,"label":"tooling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/tooling"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-alias-finder","title":"Should I Build an Alias Finder for My Commands?","sidebar_label":"Alias finder?","description":"A tool that scans all my commands and proposes sensible two-letter acronym aliases, so the helpers I reach for most get short names without me inventing them.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","shell","tooling"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Make My Browser Bookmarks Portable?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-bookmark-portability"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build Ambient Personal-Metric Displays?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-ambient-metric-displays"}},"content":"I have more commands than I have short names for. Inventing aliases by hand is haphazard, so the\\nones I use most still have long names. Let a tool propose them.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** An alias finder that scans all my commands and proposes common two-letter acronym\\naliases. It does the boring part (deriving candidate short names and spotting collisions); I just\\naccept or reject.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Enumerate all my defined commands/functions.\\n- [ ] Generate candidate two-letter acronym aliases for each.\\n- [ ] Flag collisions and propose a non-conflicting set for me to approve.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- I get a proposed alias list I can adopt wholesale, with no two aliases clashing."},{"id":"idea-ambient-metric-displays","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-ambient-metric-displays","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-ambient-metric-displays.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-ambient-metric-displays.md","title":"Should I Build Ambient Personal-Metric Displays?","description":"Surface a personal metric where I will actually glance at it: a LaMetric motivator on the desk display and a NotePlan menu-bar app showing the day\'s metrics.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"app","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/app"},{"inline":true,"label":"lametric","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/lametric"},{"inline":true,"label":"noteplan","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/noteplan"},{"inline":true,"label":"self-quantifying","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/self-quantifying"}],"readingTime":0.9,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-ambient-metric-displays","title":"Should I Build Ambient Personal-Metric Displays?","sidebar_label":"Metric displays?","description":"Surface a personal metric where I will actually glance at it: a LaMetric motivator on the desk display and a NotePlan menu-bar app showing the day\'s metrics.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","app","lametric","noteplan","self-quantifying"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build an Alias Finder for My Commands?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-alias-finder"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Make Cross-Linking Between My Notes Faster?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-fast-cross-linking"}},"content":"A metric I have to open an app to see is a metric I forget. I want the numbers I care about to\\nlive in my ambient field of view, where a glance is enough.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** Put a personal metric where I already look, two surfaces:\\n\\n- **LaMetric motivator.** An app that surfaces a personal metric on the LaMetric display on my\\n  desk, so the number I am trying to move is always in sight.\\n- **NotePlan menu bar.** A NotePlan menu-bar app that shows the day\'s metrics at a glance, so the\\n  same numbers are one look away while I work.\\n\\nBoth are the same idea (ambient, glanceable metrics) on two displays, so they likely share the\\nmetric source.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Decide the metric source the two displays read from.\\n- [ ] Build the LaMetric app that pushes a personal metric to the device.\\n- [ ] Build the NotePlan menu-bar app that shows the day\'s metrics at a glance.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- The metric I am tracking is visible at a glance on at least one ambient display, no app to open."},{"id":"idea-fast-cross-linking","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-fast-cross-linking","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-fast-cross-linking.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-fast-cross-linking.md","title":"Should I Make Cross-Linking Between My Notes Faster?","description":"Lower the friction of linking notes: variable-driven glue links in iA Writer, a copy-all-locations helper feeding pbcopy, and auto VS Code headers in NotePlan.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"notes","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/notes"},{"inline":true,"label":"knowledge-base","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/knowledge-base"}],"readingTime":0.9,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-fast-cross-linking","title":"Should I Make Cross-Linking Between My Notes Faster?","sidebar_label":"Cross-linking?","description":"Lower the friction of linking notes: variable-driven glue links in iA Writer, a copy-all-locations helper feeding pbcopy, and auto VS Code headers in NotePlan.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","notes","knowledge-base"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build Ambient Personal-Metric Displays?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-ambient-metric-displays"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build an Instagram-Metadata Scraper?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-instagram-metadata-scraper"}},"content":"The thing that stops me cross-linking notes is friction: hunting for the right path, copying it,\\npasting it in the right shape. A few small helpers would make linking nearly free.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** Three small tools that all reduce link friction:\\n\\n- **Smarter glue links.** Add variables to glue links, and integrate glue with iA Writer so the\\n  links resolve where I actually write.\\n- **Copy all locations.** A helper that adds every location to the `pbcopy` script at once, so\\n  fast cross-linking is one keystroke instead of one-path-at-a-time.\\n- **Auto headers.** A script to auto-add a VS Code header to a NotePlan calendar file, so jumping\\n  between the two editors keeps its context.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Add variable support to glue links and wire glue into iA Writer.\\n- [ ] Build the \\"copy all locations\\" helper that feeds every location into the `pbcopy` script.\\n- [ ] Script the VS Code header auto-insert for NotePlan calendar files.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- Linking to another note is one action, not a path hunt.\\n- Locations are copyable in bulk for fast cross-referencing."},{"id":"idea-instagram-metadata-scraper","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-instagram-metadata-scraper","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-instagram-metadata-scraper.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-instagram-metadata-scraper.md","title":"Should I Build an Instagram-Metadata Scraper?","description":"Extract Instagram metadata via an HTML/CSS selector pipeline, so post data I care about can be pulled programmatically instead of copied by hand.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"scraping","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scraping"},{"inline":true,"label":"instagram","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/instagram"}],"readingTime":0.61,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-instagram-metadata-scraper","title":"Should I Build an Instagram-Metadata Scraper?","sidebar_label":"Instagram scraper?","description":"Extract Instagram metadata via an HTML/CSS selector pipeline, so post data I care about can be pulled programmatically instead of copied by hand.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","scraping","instagram"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Make Cross-Linking Between My Notes Faster?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-fast-cross-linking"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Port My Portfolio to React?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-port-portfolio-to-react"}},"content":"There is metadata on Instagram posts I would like to work with programmatically, and no clean\\nway to get it short of copying by hand.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** A script to extract Instagram metadata via an HTML/CSS selector pipeline: point it\\nat a post, declare the selectors for the fields I want, and get structured data out.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Fetch a post\'s page HTML.\\n- [ ] Define an HTML/CSS selector pipeline for the metadata fields of interest.\\n- [ ] Emit the extracted fields as structured data.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- Given a post, I get its metadata fields as structured output, no manual copying.\\n\\n## Open questions\\n\\n- How resilient is selector-based scraping to Instagram\'s markup changes, and is there an\\n  official/API path that is steadier?"},{"id":"idea-port-portfolio-to-react","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-port-portfolio-to-react","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-port-portfolio-to-react.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-port-portfolio-to-react.md","title":"Should I Port My Portfolio to React?","description":"A captured idea, since actioned: port my portfolio site to React. Tracked as a shipped idea on the board so the backlog reflects what actually got done.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"react","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/react"},{"inline":true,"label":"frontend","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/frontend"},{"inline":true,"label":"portfolio","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/portfolio"},{"inline":true,"label":"web","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/web"}],"readingTime":0.55,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-port-portfolio-to-react","title":"Should I Port My Portfolio to React?","sidebar_label":"Portfolio to React?","description":"A captured idea, since actioned: port my portfolio site to React. Tracked as a shipped idea on the board so the backlog reflects what actually got done.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","react","frontend","portfolio","web"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"shipped","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build an Instagram-Metadata Scraper?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-instagram-metadata-scraper"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Make My Scripts Portable Across Machines?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-portable-scripts"}},"content":"A backlog line that I went on to act on: porting my portfolio over to React. It is here as a\\n**shipped** idea so the board shows it for what it is, done, rather than dropping it.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** Continue porting the portfolio to React: move the site off its old stack onto a\\nReact front end.\\n\\n**Status.** Actioned. This started as a captured \\"continue porting\\" line, so by the time it was\\nfiled it was already underway; it now sits in the **Shipped** column. The durable lessons from\\ndoing it belong in the relevant Craft topic; this card just records that the idea graduated from\\nbacklog to done."},{"id":"idea-portable-scripts","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-portable-scripts","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-portable-scripts.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-portable-scripts.md","title":"Should I Make My Scripts Portable Across Machines?","description":"Package my reusable scripts so a brew install brings them to any machine, and keep work tasks backed up on a schedule so nothing local-only is ever lost.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"backup","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/backup"},{"inline":true,"label":"tooling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/tooling"}],"readingTime":0.85,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-portable-scripts","title":"Should I Make My Scripts Portable Across Machines?","sidebar_label":"Portable scripts?","description":"Package my reusable scripts so a brew install brings them to any machine, and keep work tasks backed up on a schedule so nothing local-only is ever lost.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","backup","tooling"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Port My Portfolio to React?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-port-portfolio-to-react"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Self-Describing Shell-Completion System?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-shell-completion-system"}},"content":"My useful helpers live on one machine. Every new laptop means re-collecting them by hand, and\\nanything local-only is one disk failure from gone. I want my tooling and my tasks to travel with\\nme.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** Two halves of the same \\"don\'t lose my stuff\\" problem:\\n\\n- **Portable scripts.** `brew install` my own scripts so the reusable helpers travel with me\\n  across machines, and move my reusable work scripts over into that package.\\n- **Backed-up tasks.** A scheduled job that makes sure my work tasks are constantly backed up, so\\n  the task state is never trapped on a single machine.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Package my reusable scripts as a Homebrew formula (tap or local) so `brew install` sets up a\\n      new machine.\\n- [ ] Move the reusable work scripts into that package.\\n- [ ] Add a scheduled job that continuously backs up my work tasks.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- A fresh machine gets my full toolset with one `brew install`.\\n- My work tasks are recoverable from a backup taken without me thinking about it."},{"id":"idea-shell-completion-system","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-shell-completion-system","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-shell-completion-system.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-shell-completion-system.md","title":"Should I Build a Self-Describing Shell-Completion System?","description":"One generic completion mechanism every command opts into: run it with --options and it returns its own flags, generated from its own bash case statement.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"shell","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/shell"},{"inline":true,"label":"tooling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/tooling"}],"readingTime":1.16,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-shell-completion-system","title":"Should I Build a Self-Describing Shell-Completion System?","sidebar_label":"Shell completion?","description":"One generic completion mechanism every command opts into: run it with --options and it returns its own flags, generated from its own bash case statement.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","shell","tooling"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Make My Scripts Portable Across Machines?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-portable-scripts"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Slack-Thread to Clean-Markdown Exporter?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-slack-to-markdown"}},"content":"One completion mechanism, shared by every command I write, instead of hand-maintaining a\\ncompletion script per tool.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** A generic shell-completion convention: when a command runs with `--options` it\\nreturns its own list of options. Every tool opts into the same mechanism, so the date helpers,\\nthe AWS-profile switcher, and `sed-dates` all complete the same way (the AWS switcher is the\\nfirst thing to convert).\\n\\n**The clever part.** Rather than declaring the option list twice (once in the `case` statement\\nthat handles the flags, once in a completion file), parse the command\'s own bash `case`\\nstatement and auto-generate the completion options from it. The command stays the single source\\nof truth; completion is derived, never drifts.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Define the `--options` convention: a command run with `--options` prints its flags, one per\\n      line, for the completer to consume.\\n- [ ] Write the generic completer that calls `<cmd> --options` and feeds the result to the shell.\\n- [ ] Parse a bash `case` statement and auto-generate the `--options` output from it, so the case\\n      block is the only place options are declared.\\n- [ ] Convert the AWS-profile switcher to use it (first adopter), then the date helpers and\\n      `sed-dates`.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- A new command gets working tab-completion by adding nothing but its normal `case` block.\\n- The AWS switcher, the date helpers, and `sed-dates` all complete through the one mechanism."},{"id":"idea-slack-to-markdown","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-slack-to-markdown","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-slack-to-markdown.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-slack-to-markdown.md","title":"Should I Build a Slack-Thread to Clean-Markdown Exporter?","description":"A script that copies a Slack thread out as clean Markdown, so a useful discussion can land in my notes as readable prose instead of a wall of pasted chat.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"notes","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/notes"},{"inline":true,"label":"slack","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/slack"}],"readingTime":0.57,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-slack-to-markdown","title":"Should I Build a Slack-Thread to Clean-Markdown Exporter?","sidebar_label":"Slack to Markdown?","description":"A script that copies a Slack thread out as clean Markdown, so a useful discussion can land in my notes as readable prose instead of a wall of pasted chat.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","notes","slack"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Self-Describing Shell-Completion System?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-shell-completion-system"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Stale-Notes & Bad-Link Detector?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-stale-notes-detector"}},"content":"Good discussions happen in Slack threads, and I want to keep them in my notes. Pasting a thread\\nraw is unreadable; cleaning it up by hand is tedious enough that I usually do not bother.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** A script to copy a Slack thread out as clean Markdown: author, message, and\\nstructure preserved, but rendered as readable prose I can drop straight into a note.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Pull a thread\'s messages (API or export) given its link.\\n- [ ] Render them as clean Markdown (attribution + ordering, noise stripped).\\n- [ ] Put the result on the clipboard for a one-step paste into my notes.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- Copying a thread gives me note-ready Markdown with no manual cleanup."},{"id":"idea-stale-notes-detector","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/idea-stale-notes-detector","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-stale-notes-detector.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-04-13-idea-stale-notes-detector.md","title":"Should I Build a Stale-Notes & Bad-Link Detector?","description":"A regular health check over my personal book: surface stale areas by recent-edit count and catch broken links before they rot, on a multi-directory find prune.","date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"ideas","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/ideas"},{"inline":true,"label":"scripting","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scripting"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"notes","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/notes"},{"inline":true,"label":"knowledge-base","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/knowledge-base"}],"readingTime":1.1,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"idea-stale-notes-detector","title":"Should I Build a Stale-Notes & Bad-Link Detector?","sidebar_label":"Notes health check?","description":"A regular health check over my personal book: surface stale areas by recent-edit count and catch broken links before they rot, on a multi-directory find prune.","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["ideas","scripting","automation","notes","knowledge-base"],"date":"2022-04-13T00:00:00.000Z","kind":"idea","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Slack-Thread to Clean-Markdown Exporter?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-slack-to-markdown"},"nextItem":{"title":"Should I Tinker with Browser Automation?","permalink":"/thoughts/tinker-browser-automation"}},"content":"My personal book grows faster than I curate it. I want it to tell me where it is rotting\\ninstead of finding out by stumbling on a dead link or a section I forgot existed.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n**The idea.** A regular health check over the notes, two signals:\\n\\n- **Stale areas.** Run `tree` over the personal book on a schedule and surface recent-edit\\n  counts per area, so the parts I have not touched in a while stand out (highlight them\\n  accordingly).\\n- **Broken links.** A bad-link detector that runs regularly and fixes (or flags) broken links\\n  across the notes before they accumulate.\\n\\n**The shared dependency.** Both need to walk the book while skipping the noise directories, so\\nthe first real task is getting the `find` mechanic working: passing multiple directories to\\n`find`\'s prune option. That prune is the engine both the staleness scan and the link checker\\nride on.\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- [ ] Get `find`\'s multi-directory prune working (pass several dirs to prune in one invocation).\\n- [ ] Staleness scan: `tree` + per-area recent-edit counts on a schedule, highlighting stale areas.\\n- [ ] Bad-link detector: scan for broken links across the notes, run regularly.\\n\\n## Success criteria\\n\\n- I get a periodic report of which areas of the book are going stale.\\n- Broken links are caught by the checker, not by me tripping over them."},{"id":"tinker-browser-automation","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/tinker-browser-automation","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2022-01-16-tinker-browser-automation.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2022-01-16-tinker-browser-automation.md","title":"Should I Tinker with Browser Automation?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I tinker with browser-automation tools like Automa to script repetitive workflows?","date":"2022-01-16T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"browser-automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/browser-automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"automa","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automa"},{"inline":true,"label":"chrome-extension","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/chrome-extension"},{"inline":true,"label":"automation","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/automation"},{"inline":true,"label":"first-time","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/first-time"},{"inline":true,"label":"idea","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/idea"}],"readingTime":0.33,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"tinker-browser-automation","title":"Should I Tinker with Browser Automation?","sidebar_label":"Browser automation?","description":"A thought I am weighing: should I tinker with browser-automation tools like Automa to script repetitive workflows?","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["browser-automation","automa","chrome-extension","automation","first-time","idea"],"date":"2022-01-16T10:00","kind":"idea","class":"first-time","board":"ideas","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Build a Stale-Notes & Bad-Link Detector?","permalink":"/thoughts/idea-stale-notes-detector"},"nextItem":{"title":"\ud83d\udd2c What Should I Learn About Software?","permalink":"/thoughts/learning-software"}},"content":"A thought I keep coming back to: **should I tinker with browser-automation tools like Automa** to\\nscript the repetitive workflows I do by hand? I have not committed to it; here is what I am weighing.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Browser Automation\\n* [ ] Automa: youtube.com/watch?v=PmejVpMZxVg&feature=share  >2022-01-16 #2022-04-07\\n* [ ] Look into: chrome.google.com/webstore/detail/automa/infppggnoaenmfagbfknfkancpbljcca  >2022-01-16 #2022-04-07"},{"id":"learning-software","metadata":{"permalink":"/thoughts/learning-software","editUrl":"https://github.com/omars-lab/omars-lab.github.io/edit/master/bytesofpurpose-blog/thoughts/thoughts/2021-09-07-learning-software.md","source":"@site/thoughts/2021-09-07-learning-software.md","title":"\ud83d\udd2c What Should I Learn About Software?","description":"A research thought I am weighing: what should I learn about software development best practices, architecture, and scaling?","date":"2021-09-07T10:00:00.000Z","tags":[{"inline":true,"label":"software-development","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/software-development"},{"inline":true,"label":"architecture","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/architecture"},{"inline":true,"label":"best-practices","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/best-practices"},{"inline":true,"label":"research","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/research"},{"inline":true,"label":"scaling","permalink":"/thoughts/tags/scaling"}],"readingTime":1.75,"hasTruncateMarker":true,"authors":[{"name":"Omar Eid","title":"Principal AI Architect & Entrepreneur","url":"https://github.com/omars-lab","imageURL":"/img/headshot.png","key":"oeid","page":null}],"frontMatter":{"slug":"learning-software","title":"\ud83d\udd2c What Should I Learn About Software?","sidebar_label":"\ud83d\udd2c Learning software","description":"A research thought I am weighing: what should I learn about software development best practices, architecture, and scaling?","authors":["oeid"],"tags":["software-development","architecture","best-practices","research","scaling"],"date":"2021-09-07T10:00","kind":"research","board":"research","stage":"backlog","priority":"low","draft":false},"unlisted":false,"prevItem":{"title":"Should I Tinker with Browser Automation?","permalink":"/thoughts/tinker-browser-automation"}},"content":"A research thought: **what should I learn about software** to level up on best practices,\\narchitecture, and scaling? These are the questions I am gathering, and the resources I want to\\nwork through, before I dig in.\\n\\n\x3c!-- truncate --\x3e\\n\\n## Best practices\\n\\n* What does it take to start a software practice?\\n* What are the general best practices worth internalizing early?\\n\\n## Agile and craftsmanship\\n\\n* What can I learn from the agile and craftsmanship movements?\\n* Sources to read:\\n  * [Manifesto for Software Craftsmanship](https://manifesto.softwarecraftsmanship.org/)\\n  * [Principles behind the Agile Manifesto](https://agilemanifesto.org/principles.html)\\n\\n## Architectural diagrams\\n\\nThe biggest open area for me. I want to learn the different kinds of architecture diagrams and\\nwhen to reach for each.\\n\\n* What are the different architecture diagrams, and when do I use each?\\n* Is there anything I can learn from building architects (the people who design buildings)?\\n* What diagrams do others expect to see?\\n* Which diagram captures each of these dimensions, and can any single diagram hold them all?\\n  * Timing and flow\\n  * Category, data types, and transformations\\n  * Queries\\n  * Errors (hard errors vs. soft errors)\\n  * Levels of connectivity\\n  * Data dependencies and data flow\\n  * Tool usage and customer experience\\n  * Network flow and connectivity\\n  * Cost structure and cost flow: how does this project put money in the bank, and how does the\\n    business benefit from the architecture?\\n\\nSources to read:\\n\\n* [List of UML books](https://modeling-languages.com/list-uml-books/)\\n* [Introduction to Context Diagrams](https://www.modernanalyst.com/Resources/Articles/tabid/115/ID/1355/Introduction-to-Context-Diagrams.aspx)\\n* [Architectural diagrams (archisoup)](https://www.archisoup.com/studio-guide/architectural-diagrams)\\n* [Penetration testing architecture (ResearchGate)](https://www.researchgate.net/figure/Penetration-testing-architecture_fig4_254036014)\\n\\n## Learning from others\\n\\n* What general practices can I learn from blog posts and other engineers?\\n* Books: I want to read more coding books (titles to be picked).\\n* References worth following:\\n  * [Amazon\'s 2020 Letter to Shareholders](https://www.aboutamazon.com/news/company-news/2020-letter-to-shareholders)\\n  * [Omar Elgabry on Medium](https://medium.com/@OmarElgabry)\\n  * [\\"The Whacking Game\\" (TextNow Engineering)](https://medium.com/textnowengineering/the-whacking-game-ee3af79c6e13)\\n  * [David Peter\'s blog](https://david-peter.de/) and his [GitHub (sharkdp)](https://github.com/sharkdp?tab=repositories)\\n  * [A talk worth watching](https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UAKPoAn2cB0)"}]}}')}}]);